Napa Cabbage Salad

Dressing:
1/4 c tahini
2 tbsp rice vinegar (or 1 tbsp rice vinegar and 1 tbsp fresh lime juice)
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp honey or agave syrup
1 tbsp minced fresh ginger
2 tsp asian chile paste or 1/2 tsp red pepper flakes
2 tsp toasted sesame oil
2 tsp white miso paste

Using a whisk or blender, combine all ingredients. Drizzle up to 1/4 c water into the dressing and whisk or blend until it reaches your desired consistency.

Slaw:
1 head napa cabbage, shredded (3-4 c)
1 c shredded red cabbage
2 carrots, peeled and julienned
1 cucumber peeled and cut into 1/4" slices
1 red bell pepper, julienned
1 c roughly chopped fresh cilantro leaves
1/2 c roughly chopped peanuts

In a large salad bowl, toss together the cabbages, carrots, cucumber, bell pepper, and cilantro. Drizzle the dressing over the top and toss to combine, then sprinkle the peanuts over the top and serve.
